The paper discusses the issue of datasets not receiving appropriate credit in scientific publications and proposes a network flow measure, DataRank, to assign relative value to each node in the citation network. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), databases (cs.DB), and computer and society (cs.CY).
